Package edu.cnm.deepdive.teamle.model.dao

Interface UserDao

public interface UserDao
Provides CRUD operations on User entity instances. INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE operations are implemented as ReactiveX Single tasks, which execute on subscription; some SELECT tasks are implemented using LiveData queries, which execute on observation, or (if already being observed) on Room-based updates to the underlying tables; one SELECT (select(String)) is implemented as a ReactiveX Maybe task, to allow for the appropriate handling of an empty query result.

    • select

      LiveData<User> select(long id)
      Constructs and returns a LiveData-based query of a single user, using the primary key value. When observed (or when the contents of the user table are modified using Room methods), the query is executed.
      Parameters:
      id - Unique identifier (primary key value) of the User instance of interest.
      Returns:
      LiveData that can be observed for the User instance of interest.

    • select

      Maybe<User> select(String oauthKey)
      Constructs and returns a ReactiveX-based query of a single user, using the fixed OAuth2.0 identifier (subject) of the User of interest. When executed (subscribed to), the query is executed, and the result (if any) is passed to the subscribing Consumer; if the query does not return a result, then the subscribing Action.
      Parameters:
      oauthKey - OAuth2.0 identifier (subject) of the User instance of interest.
      Returns:
      Maybe that can be executed (subscribed to) to obtain the User instance of interest.

    • select

      LiveData<List<User>> select()
      Constructs and returns a LiveData-based query of all User instances, sorted by display name. When observed (or when the contents of the user table are modified using Room methods), the query is executed.
